#Innovation
Description
End-to-End Automation: Streamlined the software installation request lifecycle by integrating Service Catalog Items, Workflows, and Flow Designer, eliminating manual approvals and task assignment.
Optimized Task Handling: Automated catalog task generation and assignment to the correct IT fulfillment group based on software type and category.
Maintainability & Scalability: Designed the solution to be easily maintained by admins or future developers by leveraging out-of-the-box Flow Designer logic and clear workflow documentation.
User Experience Enhancements: Applied UI policies to dynamically display additional fields only when necessary (e.g., licensed software justification), making the request form cleaner and more user-friendly.

# Document Technical Blueprint
Description
Variables:
Software Name and Version
Business Justification / Purpose of Installation
Requested For (auto-populated with current user, but editable if requesting for others)
License Type (Free / Licensed)
Approval Use Cases:
Software Asset Team Approval required automatically when Licensed Software is selected.
IT Security Approval triggered for requests flagged as high-risk or requiring elevated permissions.
Fulfillment Task Use Cases:
Catalog tasks created for the IT Software Support group for installation.
Automatic closure of RITM once all fulfillment tasks are completed successfully.

# Document Technical Blueprint
Description
Flow Designer Workflow
Steps included: Catalog Submission → Manager Approval → Conditional Software Asset Team Approval (for licensed software) → Task Creation for IT Fulfillment → Completion & Closure.
Variable-to-Field Mapping Logic
Mapped fulfillment details into Catalog Task (sc_task) for assignment to the correct IT group.
Custom Table Schema 
Captures additional metadata related to software requests (e.g., license category, cost center).
Portal widget references (if any customizations were made)

